<item>
            <title>[SOLR-11829] [Ref-Guide] Indexing documents with existing id</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11829</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Solr Documentation for &lt;a href=&quot;http://lucene.apache.org/solr/guide/7_2/documents-screen.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Document screen&lt;/a&gt; states that if overwrite is set to false, then incoming documents with the same id would be dropped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the documentation of &lt;a href=&quot;http://lucene.apache.org/solr/guide/7_2/introduction-to-solr-indexing.html#introduction-to-solr-indexing&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Indexing&lt;/a&gt; and actual behavior states otherwise (i.e, allows the duplicate addition of documents with the same id)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
